Cruise ship passengers on today relived their two day ordeal at sea after being trapped on Carnival Spirit as Sydney was battered by the storm of the century .
Huge waves as high as 40 feet smashed glass panels , shattered plates and cups .
A Sydney harbour pilot finally boarded this morning and the ship , carrying 2,500 holidaymakers and 1,500 crew , docked at the Overseas Passenger Terminal .
The port in Sydney reopened on Wednesday morning .